2 SOUR @S261@
1 NOTE Newspaper clipping
2 DATE about 1923
2 NOTE Johnny Hayes Kissed Girl During Color Presentation
3 CONT 
3 CONT Midshipman John A. ("Snooks") Hayes accepted the den of his comrades of the regiment yesterday afternoon and planted a smart kiss upon the lips of Miss Katherine Joyce of Baltimore, during the present
3 CONC ation of the national and regimental colors at "dress parade" yesterday afternoon, so the story is going the rounds.
3 CONT 
3 CONT Hayes, be it known, is the successful cadet lieutenant and company commander of the Fifth Company, which won the annual competition and honor of carrying the colors for the next academic term. And yes
3 CONC terday's dress parade marked the official presentation. It is generally accepted that at this function the girl who makes the presentation is the "O.A.O." (One and Only) of the recipient.
3 CONT 
3 CONT While the regiment was standing at present arms, and Miss Joyce advanced on the arm of Superintendent Wilson, some of Hayes' comrades cried out, "Kiss her!" There was a huge crowd at the ceremony. Som
3 CONC e say that Hayes lost no time in going through the osculation, and it was afterwards reported that Admiral Wilson was about to call "break," but that little Hayes was a bit too fast for him.
1 EVEN
2 DATE 1924
2 NOTE Member of the 1924 Olympic boxing team
