1 NOTE The family members were all musically inclined.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Verbatim from article:
2 CONT 
2 CONT Perhaps one of the things that set the family apart was their unusual musical ability. Emanuel was a very good 'fiddler' and nearly all of the family played some instrument. Some of the played severa
2 CONC l and none had any training. They played by ear and were self taught. They formed an Achenbach dance band and played for dances for miles around all through the years. In fact there is still in 1983 a
2 CONC n Achenbach band now made up mostly of the next generation. However, Emanuel's youngest son Joe who was the saxophonist, still playes with the band at age 76 and still used the same instrument that h
2 CONC e used as a young man.
