2 SOUR @S43@
1 NOTE Joan E. Joseph sent an extract from the 1920 census of
2 CONT Schuylkill Haven.
2 CONT 
2 CONT ED 115
2 CONT Sheet 11A
2 CONT North Ward
2 CONT 38-236-242
2 CONT ACHENBACH, DANIEL, Blacksmith, 51, RR car shops, working, b.
2 CONT PA
2 CONT HANNAH (?A) Wife, 49, Lacer, textile mill, working, b. PA
2 CONT BERTHA M. dau., 32, single, no job
2 CONT VERNA R. dau. 19 (or 29?) Clerk, grocery store.
2 CONT HOMER D. son 17, Cutter, textile, working.
2 CONT KRAMER, ELLEN L. sister-in-law, 61, widow. All b. Pa. no
2 CONT occupation.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She reports that Ellen Kramer, was Ellen Reinhart and the wife
2 CONT of Lewis
2 CONT Redolphus Kramer, Minister  (son of William A. Kramer
2 CONT (1828-1876)).
2 CONT Daniel's wife was her sister Hannah Reinhart.
2 CONT They were daughters of William and Lidia [sic] (Berger)
2 CONT Reinhart.
