1 NAME John/Beer/
2 SOUR @S233@
1 SEX M
1 PROB
2 DATE 21 MAR 1782
2 PLAC Northampton County, Pennsylvania, USA
2 NOTE the same 21 March [1782, ed.]
3 CONT 
3 CONT On the petition of Enoch Beer and Adam Beer Children of
3 CONT John Beer late of Leheigh [sic] Townsip yeoman deceased setting
3 CONT forth that the petitioners said father lately died intestate
3 CONT leaving a widow to wit, Anna, and having issue, to wit, Eight
3 CONT Children, Amos, Enoch, Adam, John, Moses, Samuel, Elisabeth the
3 CONT wife of William Dieter and Susanna, of whom the said Moses and
3 CONT Samuel died in the lifetime of their said father, the said
3 CONT Moses leaving issue four children, to wit, Samuel, David, Jacob
3 CONT and Rachel, all yet under the age of twenty one years, and the
3 CONT said Samuel leaving issue two children, to wit Ann and Cleora
3 CONT both under the age of fourteen years.  And that the said
3 CONT intestate died seized in his demesne as of fee of and in a
3 CONT certain Messuage or tenement and three contiguous tracts of
3 CONT land situate in Leheigh township adjoing lands of Lingle Dewalt
3 CONT Fahringer and others containing together two hundred and fifty
3 CONT acres or thereabouts be the same more or less with the
3 CONT appurtenances;  Praying the court would be pleased to award an
3 CONT inquest to make partition of the real estate of the said
3 CONT intestate John Beer deceased to and among the said children &
3 CONT Representatives of the said intestate in such manner and in
3 CONT such proportions as by the acts of general assembly are
3 CONT directed and appointed if such partition can be made without
3 CONT prejudice to or spoiling the whole;  but if such partition
3 CONT cannot be made thereof then that the said inqest may be
3 CONT directed to value and appraise the said real estate and make
3 CONT return thereof to the said court in order for confirmation
3 CONT according to the acts of of assembly aforesaid;  Whereupon it
3 CONT considered by the court and ordered, that a writ do issue out
3 CONT of this court commanding the sherif or the said county, that
3 CONT taking with him twelve honest and lawful men of his bailiwick,
3 CONT by whom the truth of the matter may be better known, he in his
3 CONT proper person shall go to the aforesaid land, and there by the
3 CONT oath or affirmation of the said inquest, make a just and true
3 CONT partition of the said lands unto and among the children and
3 CONT Representatives of the said deceased if partition thereof can
3 CONT be made without prejudice to and spoiling the whole;  And if
3 CONT partition thereof cannot be made without prejudice to and
3 CONT spoiling the whole, that then by the oath or affirmation of the
3 CONT said inquest he the said sherif shall cause the aforesaid lands
3 CONT and premises to be valued and appraised And that the partition
3 CONT or valuation which he shall so make he diligently & openly have
3 CONT before the justices of the orphan's court to be held at easton
3 CONT in and for the said county the twentieth day of June next under
3 CONT his seal and the seals of those by whose oath or affirmation he
3 CONT shall make the said partition or valuation and that writ.___
