1 TITL Obituary of Karl Frederick Schoeller, Suess Funeral Home
1 ABBR KarlSchoellerJrObituary
1 NOTE Life Legacy
2 CONT Karl F. Schoeller, Jr., of Souderton, PA and formerly of Perkasie, PA died Wednesday, October 15, 2014 at his home. He was 83.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He was the husband of Ruth J. (Wenhold) Schoeller. The couple celebrated  their 62nd wedding anniversary on April 26, 2014.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Born in Doylestown, PA, he was the son of the late Karl F. and Mary M. (Moyer) Schoeller, Sr. A 1948 graduate of Sell-Perk High School, Perkasie, he went on to graduate from Coyne Electric School, Chi
2 CONC cago, IL in 1949.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He was a U.S. Army Veteran of the Korean War, serving at Fort Belvoir, VA, from 1953 to 1955.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Mr. Schoeller owned and operated Schoeller’s Appliance Store and was a Mechanical/Electrical Contractor in Perkasie from 1963 until his retirement in 1993, servicing several large companies in Bucks a
2 CONC nd Montgomery counties. He was a member of the Air Conditioning Contractors of America (ACCA) and the American Society of Heating, Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Engineers, Inc. (ASHRAE).
2 CONT 
2 CONT He was a member of Little Zion Lutheran Church, Telford, PA and a former member of Trinity U.C.C., Telford. He was instrumental in computerizing the cemetery records for both church cemeteries.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Mr. Schoeller served on the Board of Directors for the Perkasie Borough Authority, serving as chairman for several years. He served on the Pennridge Waste Water Treatment Authority Board of Directors
2 CONC . He was Director of Region 1 on the Pennsylvania Municipal Authorities Association. He served on the Board of Directors and was past President of the Pennridge Chamber of Commerce. He also organize
2 CONC d the Pennridge Retail Merchants Association.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He was a 50 year member of MacCalla Lodge No. 596 F&AM, Souderton, PA. He enjoyed golf.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Surviving with his wife are two sons, Jeffrey L. Schoeller and his companion Tammy, of Quakertown and Timothy K. Schoeller and his wife Brenda, of Perkasie; three daughters, Wendy E. Beck and her husb
2 CONC and Glenn, of Melbourne, FL, Christina R. Giesler and her husband the Rt. Rev. J. Christian, of Bethlehem, PA and Kathleen C. Sterner and her husband Alan, of Quakertown; 14 grandchildren, Todd, Colb
2 CONC y and Jordan Schoeller, Amanda Henry, Eric and Kyle Beck, Renee, Matthew and Casey Schoeller, Andrew and Martha Giesler, Christine, Jennifer and Allison Sterner and 6 great grandchildren. He was prece
2 CONC ded in death by a brother, John V. Schoeller.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Funeral services will be held at 11 AM on Monday, October 20, 2014 at Little Zion Lutheran Church, 267 Morwood Road, Telford, PA. Family and friends may call on Sunday evening from 6:00 – 8:00 PM at t
2 CONC he Bernard Suess Funeral Home, Inc., 606 Arch Street, Perkasie, PA or Monday morning from 10:00 to 11:00 AM at the church. Interment will be held privately in St. Andrew’s Union Cemetery, Perkasie.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Memorial contributions may be made to the American Cancer Society, 480 Norristown Road, Suite 150, Blue Bell, PA 19422.
