1 TITL Obituary of John Vincent Schoeller, Pocono Record
1 ABBR JohnVincentSchoellerObituary
1 NOTE John V. Schoeller, 71, of Lake Harmony, Kidder Township, died on Wednesday, Sept. 14, at the Gnaden Huetten Hospital in Lehighton. He is survived by his wife, Patricia (Haynes) Schoeller. They observe
2 CONC d their 47th wedding anniversary on Jan. 18.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Born in Doylestown, he was a son of the late Karl F. Sr. and Mary (Moyer) Schoeller. He grew up in Perkasie.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He graduated from Sell-Perk High School, attended MIT, and graduated from Lafayette College and Lehigh University Grad School, Bethlehem.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He worked as an electrical engineer for Western Electric, ATT, and Lucent in Allentown. After retirement, he taught at NCACC in Bethlehem. He was an avid tennis player and skier, and was a ski instruc
2 CONC tor at Jack Frost Mountain. He was a member and volunteer worker of the Musikfest Program Committee and served on the board of the Lake Harmony Concerned Citizens.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He served two years in the U.S. Army.
2 CONT 
2 CONT In addition to his wife, he is survived by a daughter, Vivian, wife of Sabino Figliuolo of Norristown; a son, Richard and his wife, Lisa of Needham, Mass.; four grandchildren; and a brother, Karl F Jr
2 CONC . of Souderton.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Memorial services will be held at 11 a.m. Monday, Sept. 19, in Saint Paul's Lutheran Church in Albrightsville, with the Rev. Manfred K. Bahmann and Rev. Anthony M. Drouncheck officiating.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Call will be from 6 to 8 p.m. Sunday, Sept. 18, in Saint Paul's Lutheran Church, Albrightsville.
2 CONT 
2 CONT In lieu of flowers, memorials donations may be made to the American Heart Association, P.O. Box 1392, Bethlehem, PA 18016 or to Habitat For Human Humanity, 239 N. Graham St., Allentown, PA 18109.
