1 TITL Obituary of Patricia Hayes, Orange County Register
1 ABBR PatKennedyHayesObituary
1 NOTE Hayes, Patricia, beloved wife, mother, grandmother, sister, aunt and friend to many, passed away peacefully on 5 July, 2008 after a prolonged illness. Pat was born on 12 August, 1930 to Patrick and Ag
2 CONC nes Kennedy in Hoboken, NJ. She married the love of her life, John A. Hayes III, in January of 1951. Pat is survived by her husband; nine children, Katherine (Dave), Tim (Sue), Greg, Claudia (Dave), R
2 CONC ick (Dayna), Gerry, Tom (Ashley), John and Matt (Julie); fifteen grandchildren; two sisters, Mildred Murphy of NJ and Janet Murphy of Arizona; numerous nieces and nephews and devoted friends. Pat wa
2 CONC s preceded in death by her beloved son, Brian, her parents and three brothers. Pat was an eager volunteer for several local organizations. She devoted her time to helping the underprivileged and child
2 CONC ren. She was a member of the Placentia Round Table Women's Club and H.I.S. House. Pat received many accolades from various groups for her unceasing work. Pat was a member of St. Joseph Catholic Churc
2 CONC h and again devoted herself to activities to benefit the church and fellow parishioners. Rosary will be held Wednesday, 9 July at 7pm and services at 10am, Thursday, 10 July at St. Joseph's Catholic C
2 CONC hurch, Placentia. Graveside services will follow at Holy Sepulcher Cemetery, Orange. In lieu of flowers, "The Patricia Hayes Community Service Scholarship Fund" is being established at El Dorado Hig
2 CONC h School. Please contact the family for more information. McAulay & Wallace Mortuary
