1 TITL Obituary of Brian Jerome Hayes, Orange County Register
1 ABBR BrianHayesObituary
1 NOTE Hayes, Brian Jerome, beloved son and brother left us to go to his Heavenly Home, Saturday night, October 21, 2006. He was born October 27, 1952 at Mary Immaculate Hospital Jamaica Queens, New York Cit
2 CONC y. Brian graduated from El Dorado High School and attended Fullerton College. He served in the U.S. Army during the Vietnam era. For many years he worked as a ride operator at Disneyland, a job he tru
2 CONC ly enjoyed. He was a big fan of NASCAR, watching races on television and attending when possible. Brian is survived by his parents, John and Patricia Hayes; sisters, Katherine Haberer and David, Claud
2 CONC ia Lewis and David; brothers, Timothy and Susan, Gregory, Patrick (Rick) and Dayna, Gerald, Thomas and Ashley, John, Matthew and Julie. Also 15 nieces and nephews, Bethany Haberer, Matthew and Cody Le
2 CONC wis, Jennifer, Karen, Kevin, Lisa, Tyler, Kelly, Brianna, Megan, Kara, Ryan, Madison, and Delaney Hayes. Services are Saturday, October 28, 11:00a.m., at St. Joseph Catholic Church, 717 Bradford Avenu
2 CONC e, Placentia. In lieu of flowers, please consider a donation in Brian's name to: HIS House Homeless Intervention and Shelter House P.O. Box 1293 Placentia, CA 92870. McAulay & Wallace Mortuary
