1 TITL Obituary Capt. John A. Hayes Jr., Retired, Morning Call
1 ABBR JohnAHayesObituary
1 TEXT Capt. John A. Hayes Jr., 84, Retired Naval Administrator, 1924 Olympic Boxer
2 CONT May 14, 1988|The Morning Call
2 CONT Retired Capt. John A. Hayes Jr., 84, of Country Meadows Retirement Home, 4011 Green Pond Road, Bethlehem Township, died Thursday in St. Luke's Hospital. He was the husband of the late Margarite (Wicke
2 CONC rsham) Mullen Hayes, the late Ruth (Wickersham) Hayes and the late Katherine (Joyce) Hayes.
2 CONT 
2 CONT A 1924 graduate of the Naval Academy, Annapolis, Md., Hayes served 20 years in the Navy and was head of the boiler division of the Navy Department's Bureau of Ships in Washington, D.C., before retirin
2 CONC g in 1946. After that, he was general sales manager of Todd Shipyards Corp. in New York City before retiring in 1969.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Also a graduate of Columbia University, he was a member of the 1924 Olympic boxing team and was a three-time intercollegiate boxing champion in the bantam weight class while attending the academy.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He was awarded the Legion of Merit and the Order of the British Empire during World War II.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Born in Port Richmond, N.Y., he was a son of the late John A. Sr. and Cecilia (Ulrich) Hayes.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Surviving are two sons, John A. III of Placentia, Calif., and James Michael of Binghamton, N.Y.; a daughter Patricia, wife of John Schoeller of Bethlehem; a sister, Mrs. Cecilia Tinsley of Palmetto, F
2 CONC la., 15 grandchildren and six great-grandchildren.
2 CONT 
2 CONT A Mass of Christian Burial will be celebrated at 10 a.m. Monday in Notre Dame of Bethlehem Catholic Church. There will be no calling hours. The Downing Funeral Home, 1002 W. Broad St., Bethlehem, is i
2 CONC n charge of arrangements.
