1 TITL Ada Elizabeth Achenbach Heinsius Simmons (1919-2008) - Grave
1 ABBR AdaElizabethAchenbachHeinsiusSimmonsGrave
1 TEXT Birth: Apr. 3, 1919, Bennett, Cedar County, Iowa, USA
2 CONT Death: Apr. 26, 2008, Iowa City, Johnson County, Iowa, USA
2 CONT 
2 CONT Ada Achenbach Heinsius Simmons, 89, West Branch, died Saturday, April 26, 2008, at Mercy Hospital in Iowa City of a stroke.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Funeral services will be 11 a.m. on Wednesday, April 30, 2008, at the Henderson-Baker Funeral Home, 201 Pedersen St. West Branch. Burial will be at Shawver Cemetery, Cedar Bluff, Iowa.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Visitation will be from 4 to 7 p.m. Tuesday, April 29, 2008, at the funeral home.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Ada was born near Bennett in rural Cedar county on April 3, 1919, the daughter of Isaac and Ethel Sproston Achenbach. She married Russell Heinsius on April 13, 1938. Three children were born to this u
2 CONC nion: James, Tom and Charles. On October 27, 1953, she was united in marriage to Delbert Simmons. There were five step children to the union; Karen, Richard, Michael, Sharon and Rosemary.
2 CONT 
2 CONT After school she went to work with Dr. Pauline Moore as her assistant for many years and help led deliver babies and give medical aid to much of the residents of rural Cedar county as well as the offi
2 CONC ce practice in Iowa City. She was a caregiver to elderly people at night, a tireless worker. She was administrator of a nursing home in Mt. Vernon and in Tipton.
2 CONT 
2 CONT In retirement she helped on the Crestview Nursing Home Advisory Board in West Branch until 2001.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She is survived by a special friend; Conrad Gregg; two sisters; Norma Long and Jean Gilliatt; two sons, James and Charles Heinsius; a sister-in-law, Gloria Achenbach and step children; Ruth Heinsius
2 CONC , Karen Gost, Michael Simmons, Sharon Jensen and Rosemary. She is also survived by 18 grandchildren and 12 great-grandchildren.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She was preceded in death by her parents; her brothers, Andrew, George and Richard Achenbach; her sister, Naomi Dvorsky; her son, Tom Heinsius, and her step-son, Richard Simmons.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Family links:
2 CONT Parents:
2 CONT Isaac Achenbach (1886-1971)
2 CONT Ethel Mary Sproston Achenbach (1898-1992)
2 CONT Spouses:
2 CONT Russell James Heinsius (1910-1963)
2 CONT Delbert Monroe Simmons (1916-1987)
2 CONT 
2 CONT Children: Thomas Richard Heinsius (1943-1959)
2 CONT 
2 CONT Burial: Shawver Cemetery, Cedar Bluff, Cedar County, Iowa, USA
