1 TITL Joyce Elaine Achenbach Conner (1945-2001) - Grave
1 ABBR JoyceElaineAchenbachConnerGrave
1 TEXT Birth: Jun. 13, 1945, USA
2 CONT Death: Jan. 28, 2001, Rapid City, Pennington County, South Dakota, USA
2 CONT 
2 CONT Joyce Elaine (Achenbach) Conner, 55, of Rapid City died Sunday, January 28, 2001. Joyce was born June 13, 1945, to Urban "Tim" and Thelma (Anthony) Achenbach.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She attended school in Sheridan, and lived here until 1970, when she moved to Butte, MT. She moved to Rapid City in 1980.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She married Kerry Conner October 28, 1989, in Rapid City. She was active in the community and loved her dogs, Rusty and Cocoa.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She was a member and past secretary of the Bethlehem Lutheran Church, a member of the Christian Women's Club, craft clubs and the Quilter's Guild. She was past-president of the Chapel Lane Homeowner
2 CONC s Association and a member of the Senior Citizens.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She was preceded in death by her parents.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Survivors include her husband, of Rapid City; a daughter, Jodie Remington of Piedmont, SD; a stepson, Kelsey Conner; a brother, Tim Achenbach of Sheridan; and three grandchildren.
2 CONT 
2 CONT A memorial service will be Friday at the Bethlehem Lutheran Church with the Rev. Bill Paepke officiating. Kinkade Funeral Chapel of Rapid City is in charge of arrangements.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Memorials have been established to the American Lung Association and the Humane Society of the Black Hills.
2 CONT 
