1 TITL Jack D. Maxted (1940-2005) - Grave
1 ABBR JackMaxtedGrave
1 TEXT Birth: Dec. 24, 1940, Sheridan, Sheridan County, Wyoming, USA
2 CONT Death: May 16, 2005, Sheridan, Sheridan County, Wyoming, USA
2 CONT 
2 CONT Jack D. Maxted, 64, of Sheridan, WY, died Monday, May 16, 2005 in Sheridan Memorial Hospital.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Mr. Maxted was born December 24, 1940 in Sheridan, WY to Wayne and Nora E. (Achenbach) Maxted. Jack grew up and attended schools in Sheridan before joining the Navy in 1958. He was discharged from th
2 CONC e Navy in 1964.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Jack returned to Sheridan, and was a truck driver for White Trucking, Tongue River Logging, and Mullinax Construction. He was also involved in stock car racing before he was involved in an accident i
2 CONC n 1968, which paralyzed him from the neck down.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Jack was a ham radio operator, enjoyed stock car racing, and spending time on the computer.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Jack was preceded in death by his father; and one nephew.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He is survived by one son, Jukie White, of Baltimore, MD; two daughters, Tammy Maxted, and Teresa Percifield, both of Gillette, WY; one brother, Pete Maxted, of Sheridan, WY; one sister, Barbara Towns
2 CONC end, of Sheridan, WY; and one grandchild.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Visitation for Mr. Maxted will be from 9:00 A.M. to 5:00 P.M. Wednesday, May 18th, and Thursday, May 19th, and from 9:00 A.M. to 12:00 noon Friday, May 20th, 2005 at Champion Ferries Funeral Home. Fun
2 CONC eral service will be 2:00 P.M. Friday, May 20th at Champion Ferries Funeral Home with the Rev. Douglas Goodwin officiating. Interment will be in the Sheridan Municipal Cemetery. Arrangements are wit
2 CONC h Champion Ferries Funeral Home.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Memorials in memory of Mr. Maxted may be made to the Sheridan College Rodeo Club, in care of Karen Green, First Interstate Bank, P. O. Box 2007, Sheridan, WY 82801
2 CONT 
