1 TITL Harry Ellis Aughenbaugh (1925-2005) - Grave
1 ABBR HarryEllisAughenbaughGrave
1 TEXT Birth: Aug. 22, 1925
2 CONT Death: Dec. 16, 2005
2 CONT 
2 CONT Harry Ellis Aughenbaugh, Jr., 80, died Friday, December 16, 2005, at his
2 CONT home. He was the loving husband of Gloria (Williams) Aughenbaugh. The
2 CONT couple was married March 14, 1947, at Grace Reformed Church by the Rev.
2 CONT Irvin Raubenhold. Born in Bywood, Upper Darby, Delaware County, on August
2 CONT 22, 1925, he was the son of the late Harry Ellis and Florence Ruth
2 CONT (Harnish) Aughenbaugh. Mr. Aughenbaugh moved to York in 1938. He was a
2 CONT 1943 graduate of William Penn High School. He attended East Central State
2 CONT Teachers College in Enid, Okla., while in the service. He also attended
2 CONT Penn State. Harry retired in 1982 after 39 years of service with York
2 CONT Division-Borg Warner where he was employed as a draftsman and department
2 CONT manager. Mr. Aughenbaugh enlisted in the aviation cadet program in January,
2 CONT 1944, and served in the USAAF until November, 1945. Mr. Aughenbaugh was a
2 CONT member of Grace United Church of Christ. He organized the former Boy Scout
2 CONT Troop 55 at Grace U.C.C. and served as troop leader. He was the past
2 CONT Commodore of the Susquehanna Yacht Club and was active in several Masonic
2 CONT organizations. He was a life member of Zeredatha Lodge 451 F and AM and
2 CONT past Thrice Illustrious Master of Royal & Select Masters Lodge 21. He was
2 CONT also a member of Heritage Trust of York County, LSS Auxiliary, charter
2 CONT member of the South Central Pennsylvania Genealogical Society, member of
2 CONT Viking Athletic Association, West York VFW Post 8951, the York County
2 CONT S.P.C.A. and Friends of the Air Force Museum. In addition to his wife,
2 CONT Mr. Aughenbaugh leaves his daughter, Pamela Lorraine Nester and husband,
2 CONT David; granddaughter, Julie Lorraine Russell and husband, Clifford, and
2 CONT greatgrandsons, Luke Aaron Russell and Noah Ryan Russell, all of Baton
2 CONT Rouge, LA; grandson, Andrew David Nester and wife, Rachel, great-grandson,
2 CONT Michael Andrew Nester and great granddaughter, Sydney Raine Nester, all of
2 CONT Walker, LA; and grandson, Jonathan David Nester of Olympia, WA. Memorial
2 CONT service at a later date. Private burial in Prospect Hill Cemetery.
2 CONT [York Daily Record]
2 CONT 
