1 TITL Pamela Aughenbaugh Nester (1948-2014) - Grave
1 ABBR PamelaAughenbaughNesterGrave
1 TEXT Birth: Jan. 1, 1948, York, York County, Pennsylvania, USA
2 CONT Death: Nov. 5, 2014, Baton Rouge, East Baton Rouge Parish, Louisiana, USA
2 CONT 
2 CONT Pamela Aughenbaugh Nester passed away peacefully at her home in Baton Rouge on November 5, 2014. Pamela was born in York, Pennsylvania to Harry E. Aughenbaugh and Gloria Williams Aughenbaugh on Januar
2 CONC y 1, 1948.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She was a graduate of York Suburban High School and Penn State University. She and her husband, David, moved to Baton Rouge in 1971. Pamela worked as a teacher and administrator in East Baton Rouge Pa
2 CONC rish until 1997. During her career, she also earned two post-graduate degrees in Education from LSU. Pamela was a member of Broadmoor United Methodist. She was a big LSU fan and loved spending time wi
2 CONC th her family.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Pamela is survived by her husband, David Nester; her children, Julie Russell and husband Clifford, Andrew Nester and wife Rachel and Jonathan Nester; her grandchildren, Michael Nester, Luke Russell, S
2 CONC ydney Nester and Noah Russell; and mother, Gloria Williams Aughenbaugh and husband Phil Knobloch.
2 CONT 
2 CONT She is preceded in death by her father, Harry E. Aughenbaugh.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Visiting hours will be observed at Resthaven Funeral Home, 11817 Jefferson Hwy, on Wednesday, November 12, 2014 from 10:00am until service time. Funeral Services will be held at 12:00pm, conducted b
2 CONC y Reverend Ken Carroll. Interment will follow in Resthaven Gardens of Memory.
