1 TITL Louis M. Kessler (-2009) - Obituary
1 ABBR LouisMKesslerObituary
1 TEXT MIDDLEBORO Louis M. Kessler, entered into rest Oct. 7, 2009, of Middleboro, formerly of Quincy, where he attended school. He was the husband of Minnie (Freedman) Kessler for 60 years; devoted father o
2 CONC f Richard Kessler of Rochester and Robert Kessler and his wife Marcia of Rochester; dear brother of Florence Eaton of Millis and the late Max Kessler and Bella Kessler; loving grandfather of Jerzy an
2 CONC d Nathaniel. He was a U.S. Army veteran of World War II, having served in the European Theatre. Services were held at the Schlossberg-Solomon Memorial Chapel, 824 Washington St., Canton, Friday, Oct
2 CONC . 9. In lieu of flowers, remembrances in his memory may be made to the charity of ones choice. Schlossberg -Solomon Chapel
