1 TITL Obituary Charlotte Deines
1 ABBR CharlotteDeinesObit
1 TEXT http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/providence/obituary.aspx?page=lifestory&pid=185680244
2 CONT 
2 CONT From the Providence Journal, 2 JUN 2017
2 CONT 
2 CONT DEINES, CHARLOTTE ELISABETH
2 CONT 83, of Waldoboro, Maine, passed away peacefully with her loving family by her side on Sunday, May 28, 2017. She loved spending time with her grandchildren most of all. Charlotte is survived by her dev
2 CONC oted husband of 63 years, Roy Deines, daughters, Linda Klemer of Warren, Sandra Deines of Farmington, NH and Cheryl Ferreira and husband Mark of Bristol, RI, grandchildren Joshua Klemer, Austin Klemer
2 CONC , Derek Deines and wife Bianca, Kaleb Travers, Peter Ferreira and wife Megan, Nicholas Ferreira and Lauren Ferreira. To extend online condolences, please visit,
0 @S444@ SOUR
1 TITL Birth Announcement Seth Griffin
1 ABBR SethGriffinBirth
1 TEXT From Rhode Island Herald, 9 JUN 1988
2 CONT 
2 CONT Mr. and Mrs. R. Griffin, Jr. Announce Birth
2 CONT 
2 CONT Mr. and Mrs. Richard A. Griffin, Jr. of Warwick announce the birth of their son, Seth Michael on May 18, 1988.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Maternal grandparents are Mrs. Edith F. Carczeri of Warwick and Mr. Bernard H. Klemer of Pawtucket. Maternal great-grandmother is Mrs. Gertrude Klemer of Providence. Paternal grandparents are Mr. an
2 CONC d Mrs. Richard A. Griffin of Warwick.
0 @S445@ SOUR
1 TITL Findagrave record for William Gilstein, Lincoln Park Cemetery
1 ABBR WilliamGilsteinFindagrave
1 TEXT Mr. Gilstein was employed by the City of Providence in code enforcement, retiring in 1980, and was a member of the City of Providence 1033 Union. He had been associated with his brothers, Benjamin Gil
2 CONC stein of Cranston and the late Cyrus Gilstein, at Gil's and Troup's Hardware, on Smith Street, for more than 15 years. A ventriloquist and magician during World War II, he performed at many nightclubs
2 CONC , Army bases and charity events in New England as "Will Gill." He was a member of the American Guild of Variety Artists, the Society of American Magicians, the Providence Hebrew Free Loan Associatio
2 CONC n and the Cranston Seniors Guild. Mr. Gilstein was a former member of Temple Emanu-El.
2 CONT 
2 CONT He was the husband of Rosalie (Chernick) Gilstein. Born in Providence, a son of the late Aaron and Rose (Stoneberg) Gilstein. Besides his wife and brother, he leaves two daughters, Gayle S. Nevins o
2 CONC f Scottsdale, Ariz., and Cheryl L. Gilstein of Providence; two sisters, Doris Reffkin and Evelyn Weinberg, both of Providence; and a granddaughter. He was a brother of the late Alton Gilstein and gran
2 CONC dfather of the late Marc J. Nevins.
0 TRLR
